There is something very peculiar about Kali Tal's approach. I have been searching for words to express my feelings toward the preamble of the SIXTIES-L e-mail forum. This is a moderated forum. This means that there are filters which introduce a bias in the entire process. What follows is from the preamble to the web page about the forum:<br><br>
&quot;SIXTIES-L is a moderated electronic mail forum for interdisciplinary academic and literary<br>
discussion of the cultural, social, and political movements of the Sixties. We invite participation<br>
from scholars in the various disciplines, such as history, literature, area studies, women's studies,<br>
african american studies, sociology, economics, political science, religion, psychology, queer<br>
studies, cultural studies etc. We also encourage the participation of teachers, artists and activists.&quot;<br><br>
These words elicit feelings identical to feelings I experienced when I came across a 1962 Radio Moscow advertisement, which stated:<br><br>
&quot;To the microphones of Moscow Radio come USSR's statesmen, prominent Soviet Russian scientists and cultural personalities, plus foreign guests - politicians and other public personalities, representatives of business circles, scientists, artists, workers, peasants, and clergy.&quot;<br><br>
Cyberspace and shortwave are different media, but the element of control and contrivance makes its appearance in both examples. Although 35 years separate these words, they convey the same feelings of a left wing controlled view of the world and who are also considered worthy participants in that world by those in control.<br><br>
I take serious note that Kali Tal invites &quot;activists&quot;, but not Vietnam Combat Veterans. Perhaps I am permitting a degree of oversensitivity to show here, but the obvious controlled &quot;acamdemic&quot; atmosphere of the entire effort would be clearly &quot;offended&quot; by a point of view that might not be  nice, but very real. If academia cannot be adult enough to sort the wheat from the chaf without a fish filter, then their points of view are indeed corrupted and are not to be trusted as reliable barometers of the truth.<br><br>
The comments alleged to be those of Kali Tal about this site add validation to this point of view if the words are truly her own.<br><br>
Yuck!   
